LLM-Generated Code Notice (written 2026-03-10)

Portions of the code in this repo were generated by an LLM (a.k.a. "generative AI"), 
such as Claude Code, or similar. In a recent action by the US Supreme Court,
they declined to hear an appeal on a case disputing the US Copyright Office denying 
grant of copyright on an AI-generated image, because the images lacked a human
author. This implies that regardless of whether a work could normally be 
copyrighted, if "created" by an LLM, it is not eligible for copyright protection.
This may change in the future, as the case law around LLMs and "AI" creations
is tested in the courts.

- Copyright Office Letter of Refusal:
  https://web.archive.org/web/20260303164310/https://www.copyright.gov/rulings-filings/review-board/docs/a-recent-entrance-to-paradise.pdf
- The Verge article about the Supreme Court action:
  https://web.archive.org/web/20260308162549/https://www.theverge.com/policy/887678/supreme-court-ai-art-copyright

Accordingly, it would currently seem that the portions of this code generated by 
LLMs is not eligible for protection and cannot meaningfully be licensed. These 
portions may be identified by commit messages that indicate the code was 
co-authored by the LLM. All other portions, written by human contributors, are 
covered by the MIT License above.

If the law changes in the future, and copyright is allowed on the LLM-generated 
code, I hereby pre-emptively assign any such code to be covered by the 
MIT License above.
